SBOM UPLOAD TO DEPENDENCY-TRACK - FINAL SCRIPT & CONFIG
================================================================================


FILE 1: .env
================================================================================
Save as: .env

# Docker Registry credentials
REGISTRY_HOST="docker.io"
REGISTRY_USER="your-docker-username"
REGISTRY_PASS="your-docker-password"

# Dependency-Track
DT_URL="http://127.0.0.1:8081"
API_KEY="your-dependency-track-api-key"

# Single Project UUID - all images upload to same project
# Get UUID from DT UI: Projects -> click project -> copy UUID from browser URL
UUID_PROJECT="xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"

# Images to scan - all using same project UUID
# Format: "registry/image:tag|project-name|project-uuid"
IMAGES=(
  "docker.io/vantage/postgres:16-alpine|postgres|${UUID_PROJECT}"
  "docker.io/library/nginx:latest|nginx|${UUID_PROJECT}"
  "docker.io/library/redis:7-alpine|redis|${UUID_PROJECT}"
  "docker.io/library/mysql:8.0|mysql|${UUID_PROJECT}"
  "docker.io/library/alpine:latest|alpine|${UUID_PROJECT}"
)


FILE 2: sbom-upload.sh
================================================================================
Save as: sbom-upload.sh

#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail
source .env
docker login "$REGISTRY_HOST" -u "$REGISTRY_USER" -p "$REGISTRY_PASS"
for ENTRY in "${IMAGES[@]}"; do
  IFS='|' read -r IMAGE PROJECT UUID <<< "$ENTRY"
  NAME=$(basename "$IMAGE" | cut -d: -f1); SBOM="/tmp/sbom-${NAME}.json"
  docker pull "$IMAGE" && trivy image --format cyclonedx --output "$SBOM" --insecure "$IMAGE"
  echo "Uploading: $NAME | Project: $PROJECT | UUID: $UUID"
  HTTP=$(curl -sk -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" -X POST "${DT_URL}/api/v1/bom" -H "X-Api-Key: ${API_KEY}" -F "project=${UUID}" -F "bom=@${SBOM}")
  echo "Done: $NAME -> HTTP $HTTP"
done


SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
================================================================================

1. Fill in .env with your actual values:
     - REGISTRY_USER / REGISTRY_PASS  -> your Docker credentials
     - API_KEY                         -> DT UI: Administration -> Access Management -> Teams
     - UUID_PROJECT                    -> DT UI: Projects -> click project -> copy UUID from URL

2. Add or remove images in IMAGES list as needed

3. Make script executable:
     chmod +x sbom-upload.sh

4. Run:
     ./sbom-upload.sh

5. Expected output per image:
     Uploading: redis | Project: redis | UUID: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
     Done: redis -> HTTP 200

6. Verify in DT UI:
     http://127.0.0.1:8080 -> Projects -> click project -> Components / Vulnerabilities tabs


TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================
HTTP 200 = Success
HTTP 400 = UUID is empty - check UUID_PROJECT is set in .env
HTTP 401 = Wrong API key - check API_KEY in .env
HTTP 404 = Wrong UUID - project not found in DT
HTTP 415 = Media type error - do not add Content-Type header manually
HTTP 000 = Cannot connect - check DT_URL and docker containers are running

Check containers:   docker ps | grep depend
Test connection:    curl -sk http://127.0.0.1:8081/api/version
List projects:      curl -sk http://127.0.0.1:8081/api/v1/project -H "X-Api-Key: YOUR_KEY"
Check SBOM file:    ls -lh /tmp/sbom-*.json

